{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, (Dąbrowska & Divjak, 2019) define Krashen's Input Hypothesis as follows:",
    "Learners progress by understanding input containing structures slightly beyond their current competence level.",
    "Comprehensible input is necessary for acquisition to occur.",
    "Input becomes comprehensible as a result of simplification and with the aid of contextual and extralinguistic cues.",
    "Speaking is a result of acquisition, not the cause; learners' production does not directly contribute to acquisition."
  ]
}